<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 13 at 5:56AM CDT until April 13 at 6:15AM CDT by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 615 AM CDT
FOR SOUTH CENTRAL ASHLEY COUNTY IN SOUTHEASTERN ARKANSAS AND NORTH
CENTRAL MOREHOUSE PARISHES...
At 555 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Berlin, or 9
miles southeast of Crossett, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Berlin.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
